<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-233-622  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 233 622.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  April 24 1989 v10 n17 p24(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Financial managers view CA's new 'Masterpiece.' (enterprise-wideintegration) (Computer Association International Inc.) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Conlon, Theresa.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Computer Associates International Inc (CA) introduced the improvedversion of their Masterpiece financial applications package to2,000 financial users via teleconference from New York.andO;Masterpiece 2.0 is targeted to multinational organizations seekinga software system that is portable across mixed computingenvironments.andP;  It consists of general ledger, accounts payable andreceivable, purchasing, inventory control and fixed-assetspackages.andP;  The concepts of portability across disparate hardwareand consistent interface between various financial applicationswas viewed favorably by many of the managers, though someexpressed concerns about the ease of conversion stressed by CA.andO;Another strength of the new system seems to be its integration tothe mainframe, which contributes to ease of access.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Computer Associates International Inc. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    CA.andO;Product:   Masterpiece 2.0 (Financial software) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionEnhancementsFinancial Software.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>